    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so if originalism is a legit scholarly approach, how do people reconcile it with the idea that the founders couldn't have possibly foreseen modern issues like digital privacy or advanced technology? does originalism have any real flexibility for those kinds of new problems, or does it just fail to adapt?",
